definition.value: An organophosphate oxoanion that results from the removal of a proton from the phosphate group of 3-O-(6-O-alpha-D-xylosylphospho-alpha-D-mannopyranosyl)-alpha-D-mannopyranose.
Any benzoate anion carrying one or more amido substituents.
Any D-hexose 6-phosphate in which the hexose is in the pyranose form.
A dihydroxy- and monomethoxy-flavone in which the hydroxy groups are positioned at C-5 and C-7 and the methoxy group is at C-6.
A nitrile formed formally by substitution of a cyano group at C-2 of butane.
The glycosyloxyflavone which is the 7-O-glucuronide of oroxylin A.
A cyclopentenyl fatty acid consisting of undecanoic acid having a cyclopent-2-enyl group at the 11-position.
Any carvone having one of its C=C double bonds reduced.
A cyclopentenyl fatty acid composed of 6-tridecenoic acid having a 2-cyclopentenyl ring at position 13.
The monocarboxylic acid anion that is the conjugate base of oroxylin A 7-O-beta-D-glucuronide.
An optically active form of hydnocarpic acid having (R)-configuration.
A 13-cyclopent-2-en-1-yltridec-6-enoic acid having R-configuration and a cis-double bond at position 6.

A sesquiterpene consisting of a tricyclo[2.2.1.0(2,6)]heptane skeleton substituted by methyl groups at positions 1 and 7 and by a 4-methylpent-3-en-1-yl group at position 7 (the 1S,2R,4S,6R,7R diastereoisomer).

A sesquiterpene consisting of a bicyclo[3.1.1]heptane skeleton substituted at position 2 by a methylidene group and at position 6 by methyl and 4-methylpent-3-en-1-yl groups (the all-S diastereoisomer).
A cis-alpha-bergamotene that has (S,S,S)-configuration.
An ortho-fused bicyclic hydrocarbon with a structure consisting of decalin hydrogenated across C(7)-C(8) and with methyl groups at C(1) and C(4a) which both have S configuration.
A silicon hydroxide in which a silicon atom is bonded to a single hydroxy function and to at least one organyl group.
A ubiquinol in which the polyprenyl substituent is octaprenyl.
A ubiquinone whose structure comprises a 2,3-dimethoxy-5-methylbenzoquinone nucleus (common to all ubiquinones) and a side chain of eight isoprenoid units.
A menaquinol whose structure comprises a 2-methylbenzohydroquinone nucleus and a side chain of eight isoprenoid units.
A sesquiterpene that is 1,6-dimethyl-4-(propan-2-yl)naphthalene in which the naphthalene ring has been hydrogenated at the 1, 2, 3, 4, 4a and 7 positions (the 1S,4R,4aS diastereoisomer).

A carbobicyclic compound that is cis-decalin substituted by a propan-2-yl group at position 1, methyl groups at position 4 and 7, and a hydroxy group at position 4a, and containing a double bond between positions 7 and 8 (the 1R,4S,4aR,8aS diastereoisomer).
A carbobicyclic compound that is 1,2,3,4,4a,5-hexahydronaphthalene which is substituted at position 1 by a propan-2-yl group and at positions 4 and 7 by methyl groups (the 1R,4R,4aS-diastereoisomer).

A carbobicyclic compound that is 1,2,3,4,4a,5,6,7-octahydronaphthalene which is substituted at positions 1, 4, and 7 by a propan-2-yl, methyl and methylidene groups, respectively (the 1R,4R,4aS-diastereoisomer).
Any cyclitol having one or more alcoholic hydroxy groups replaced by substituted or unsubstituted amino groups.

A carbotricyclic compound and sesquiterpene that is 1,2,3,3a,4,5,8,8a-octahydro-4,8-methanoazulene that is substituted by methyl groups at the 3a, 4, 7 and 8a positions (the 3aR,4R,8R,8aS-diastereoisomer).
A sulfamic acid having a phenyl group attached to nitrogen.
An organic heterotricyclic compound with a skeleton derived from a pyridine ring fused to an isoquinoline.
An organic anion resulting from deprotonation of any carboxyalkyl phosphate.
The zwitterion of L-cysteinylglycine resulting from the transfer of a proton from the hydroxy group of glycine to the amino group of cysteine. Major microspecies at pH 7.3.
A dipeptide consisting of glycine having an L-prolyl group attached to its alpha-amino nitrogen.
The zwitterion of L-prolinylglycine resulting from the transfer of a proton from the hydroxy group of glycine to the amino group of proline. Major microspecies at pH 7.3.
Any organic molecular entity derived from a fatty acid.

An organophosphate oxoanion that is the trianion formed from L-ascorbic acid 6-phosphate by deprotonation of the 3-hydroxy group and of both hydroxy groups of the phosphate function; principal species at pH 7.3.

A carbotricyclic compound and sesquiterpene that is 1a,2,3,4,4a,5,6,7b-octahydro-1H-cyclopropa[e]azulene which is substituted by methyl groups at positions 1, 1, 4 and 7 (the 1aR,4R,4aR,7bS- diastereoisomer). It has been isolated from several plant species such as Anaphalis nubigena and  Jatropha ribifolia.

A carbobicyclic compound and sesquiterpene that is 1,2,3,4,4a,5,6,7-octahydronaphthalene which is substituted a prop-1-en-2-yl group at position 3 and by methyl groups at positions 4a and 5  (the 3R,4aS,5R- diastereoisomer).
An aldonolactone phosphate that is the 6-phosphate ester of L-ascorbic acid.

A member of the class of bilenes that is 1,2,3,21-tetrahydro-5,7-ethanobilene-a-19(16H),5(2)-dione which is substituted at positions 2, 8, 13 and 18 by methyl groups and at positions 1, 3, 12 and 17 by carboxy, 2-carboxyethyl, ethyl and vinyl groups, respectively (the 1S,2S,3S diastereoisomer).
Any biologically active signalling molecule made by oxygenation of C20 fatty acids other than the classic icosanoids (the leukotrienes and the prostanoids).
Any C20 polyunsaturated fatty acid having four double bonds and at least one oxo group.
A 3-demethylubiquinol in which the polyprenyl chain contains 8 prenyl units.
A dicarboxylic acid dianion that results from the removal of a proton from each of the carboxylic acid groups of dinoflagellate luciferin.

A member of the class of bilenes that is 1,2,3,21-tetrahydro-5,7-ethanobilene-a-19(16H),5(1),5(2)-trione which is substituted at positions 2, 8, 13 and 18 by methyl groups and at positions 1, 3, 12 and 17 by carboxy, 2-carboxyethyl, ethyl and vinyl groups, respectively (the 1S,2S,3S diastereoisomer).
A dicarboxylic acid dianion that results from the removal of a proton from each of the carboxylic acid groups of oxidized dinoflagellate luciferin.
Any halo fatty acid containing at least one bromo substituent.

A member of the class of imidazoles that is methimazole in which the nitrogen bearing a hydrogen is converted into its ethoxycarbonyl derivative. A prodrug for methimazol, carbimazole is used for the treatment of hyperthyroidism.
A glycoside comprising beta-lactose having a p-(p-dimethylaminophenylazo)phenyl group at the 1-position.

A branched amino tetrasaccharide consisting of a sialyl residue, linked (2->3) to a galactosyl residue that in turn is linked (1->4) to a glucosaminyl residue, which is also carrying a fucosyl residue at the 3-position.

An amino pentasaccharide consisting of beta-D-galactose at the reducing end having a beta-D-glucosyl residue at the 4-position and an N-acetyl-alpha-neuraminyl-(2->3)-beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosyl moiety at the 3-position.
